<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:id="Course-Schedule" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title> Proposed Course Schedule</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
        The schedule below is a tentative outline of the topics we will cover in class. 
        It is subject to change based on the needs of the class and the pace at which we are able to cover material. 
        We will discuss any changes to the schedule in class and post updates on our course website.

        <table><title>Proposed Course Schedule</title>
    <tabular>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 1
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Introduction to the course, introduction to whole numbers.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 2
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Operations with whole numbers.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 3
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Order of operations, introduction to integers, operations with integers.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 4
            </cell>
            <cell>
                More operations with integers, introduction to algebraic expressions.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 5
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Exam 1
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 6
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Lots of snow, no class.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 7
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Linear equations, introduction to fractions.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 8
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Spring break, no class.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 9
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Operations with fractions, applications of fractions.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 10
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Introduction to decimals, Exam 2.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 11
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Operations with decimals, applications of decimals, introduction to ratios, rates, and proportions.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 12
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Different measurement systems, unit conversions, and an introduction to percents.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 13
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Exam 3
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 14
            </cell>
            <cell>
                Applications of percents, probability, introduction to geometry.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell>
                Week 15
            </cell>
            <cell>
                More geometry, review for final exam.
            </cell>
        </row>
        </tabular></table>
    </p>
  </introduction>
</section>